nc the fund invests in the fixed income markets across the globe it primarily invests in convertible bonds of us and foreign companies which have either relatively short remaining maturities or have a guarantee of principal by the issuer the fund invests in the securities with remaining maturities of less than seven years it invests in the less than investment grade securities with a rating between bb and b by sp bb and b by fitch and ba and b by moody’s the fund employs quantitative and fundamental analysis and focuses on f miller investment trust  miller convertible bond fund is an openended fixed income mutual fund launched and managed by wellesley investment advisors inc the fund invests in the fixed income markets across the globe it primarily invests in convertible bonds of us and foreign companies which have either relatively short remaining maturities or have a guarantee of principal by the issuer the fund invests in the securities with remaining maturities of less than seven years it invests in the less than investment grade securities with a rating between bb and b by sp bb and b by fitch and ba and b by moody’s the fund employs quantitative and fundamental analysis and focuses on factors such as issuer’s creditworthiness default risk of the convertible bonds using traditional credit analysis analyzing the convertible’s underlying common stock to determine its capital appreciation potential assessing the riskreturn potential of the convertible bond evaluating the convertible security’s impact on the overall composition of the fund’s portfolio financial soundness ability to make interest and dividend payments earnings and cashflow forecast growth trends financial health including debt to equity ratios return on equity return on assets and return on invested capital and market multiples including priceearnings ratios and priceearningsgrowth ratios to create its portfolio it benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the barclays us aggregate bond in